0want%20to%20sit%20together%20in%20a%20typical%20three-seat%20row%2C%20one%20of%20us%20will%20end%20up%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairplane-middle-seat-not-bad-aisle-window-travel-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edreaded%20middle%20seat%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20being%20next%20to%20the%20aisle%20is%20basically%20a%20non-negotiable%20for%20me%2C%20I'll%20instead%20book%20two%20aisle%20seats%20directly%20across%20from%20one%20another.%20This%20way%2C%20we're%20still%20close%20enough%20to%20chat%20and%20feel%20like%20we're%20traveling%20together%2C%20but%20we%20still%20have%20a%20decent%20amount%20of%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20(riskier)%20strategy%20is%20to%20book%20the%20window%20and%20aisle%20of%20the%20same%20row%20%E2%80%94%20if%20you're%20lucky%2C%20the%20middle%20seat%20might%20remain%20empty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cc01609-fd1f-4b1d-99f1-8aa90301b2bd%5C%22%3EIf%20I%20have%20a%20connecting%20flight%20to%20catch%2C%20I%20choose%20an%20aisle%20seat%20toward%20the%20front%20of%20the%20plane%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20on%20many%20trips%20where%20the%20flight%20attendant%20gets%20on%20the%20intercom%20to%20ask%20most%20passengers%20to%20remain%20seated%20while%20several%20people%20with%20tight%20connections%20deboard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20I've%20often%20seen%20that%20request%20ignored.%20So%2C%20if%20I%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-travel-mistake-booking-own-transfer-flight-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econnecting%20flight%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20catch%20and%20only%20an%20hour%20or%20so%20to%20do%20it%2C%20I%20book%20an%20aisle%20seat%20as%20close%20to%20the%20front%20of%20the%20cabin%20as%20possible.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20extra%20few%20minutes%20when%20everyone%20is%20fiddling%20with%20their%20overhead%20luggage%20could%20mean%20the%20difference%20between%20making%20or%20missing%20my%20next%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228db2dffe-3142-485e-a38a-904ee0de7f69%5C%22%3EIf%20my%20preferred%20seats%20are%20taken%2C%20I%20try%20to%20be%20far%20from%20a%20bathroom%20or%20galley%2C%20where%20people%20typically%20congregate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lit-up%20lavatory%20sign%20in%20plane%20cabin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6813ead3c6ad288d147fc9d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20don't%20want%20to%20spend%20my%20flight%20near%20a%20toilet.%20%3Cp%3EThamKC%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%20seat%20by%20a%20bathroom%20isn't%20preferable%20for%20several%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20passengers%20might%20be%20lining%20up%20throughout%20the%20flight%20to%20wait%20to%20use%20it.%20This%20means%20spending%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20flight%20with%20butts%20near%20your%20face.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20also%20frequently%20hear%20the%20toilet%20flushing%20and%20bad%20aromas%20may%20waft%20out%20the%20door%2C%20neither%20of%20which%20goes%20well%20with%20your%20pretzels%20and%20ginger%20ale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20also%20avoid%20sitting%20near%20a%20galley%20area%2C%20which%20can%20also%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20foot%20traffic%20because%20it's%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflight-attendant-best-and-worst-things-about-job-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflight%20attendants%3C%2Fa%3E%20prep%20the%20food%20and%20beverage%20service.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20spot%20is%20convenient%20if%20you%20want%20to%20grab%20another%20drink%20or%20get%20your%20meal%20quickly%2C%20but%20it%20can%20get%20noisy%20and%20busy.%20This%20is%20especially%20important%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20if%20you're%20a%20light%20sleeper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-seats-on-plane-which-