%20trees%20are%20hardy%2C%20tall%2C%20and%20evergreen%20%E2%80%94%20ideal%20for%20the%20region.%20Once%20planted%2C%20they%20take%20two%20to%20three%20years%20to%20mature.%20But%20the%20reward%20is%20long-lasting%3A%20%E2%80%9CA%20single%20tree%20can%20yield%2015%20to%2020%20kg%20of%20leaves%20every%20year%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20next%2025%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20Barman%20says%20with%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20farmers%20lease%20out%20their%20bay%20leaf%20gardens%20to%20traders%20for%20three%20years.%20In%20return%2C%20these%20traders%20handle%20everything%20%E2%80%94%20from%20hiring%20labourers%20and%20maintaining%20the%20trees%20to%20pest%20control%2C%20harvesting%2C%20packaging%2C%20and%20even%20transportation.%20For%20farmers%20like%20Barman%2C%20it%20means%20less%20stress%2C%20more%20support%2C%20and%20a%20more%20secure%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20sapling%20to%20spice%3A%20What%20it%20takes%20to%20grow%20bay%20leaf%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBay%20leaf%20trees%20may%20look%20unassuming%2C%20but%20they%20are%20incredibly%20rewarding%20for%20those%20who%20nurture%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20sapling%20grows%20to%20a%20height%20of%201.5%E2%80%932%20feet%20annually%2C%20while%20a%20tree%20can%20grow%20to%20over%2020%E2%80%9330%20feet%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Sukumar%20Barman.%20%E2%80%9CA%2010-foot-tall%20tree%20can%20produce%20seven%20to%20eight%20kilograms%20of%20leaves.%20It%20grows%20well%20in%20loamy%20soil.%20The%20quality%20of%20soil%20and%20dry%20weather%20determine%20the%20size%20of%20a%20leaf%2C%20which%20is%20thick%2C%20fibrous%2C%20shiny%2C%20about%201.5%E2%80%932%20inches%20wide%2C%20and%205%E2%80%938%20inches%20long.%20It%20is%20olive%20green%2C%20dark%20green%2C%20and%20light%20brown.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20harvest%20season%20runs%20from%20August%20to%20December%2C%20but%20the%20frequency%20depends%20on%20how%20quickly%20the%20leaves%20mature.%20%E2%80%9CHarvesting%20occurs%20every%20six%20to%20eight%20months%20%E2%80%94%20even%20twice%20a%20year%20in%20some%20cases%2C%E2%80%9D%20Barman%20adds.%20Once%20plucked%2C%20the%20leaves%20are%20left%20to%20dry%20for%20three%20to%20four%20sunny%20days.%20But%20the%20monsoon%20season%20brings%20its%20own%20set%20of%20hurdles.%20%E2%80%9CCovering%20the%20leaves%20with%20plastic%20sheets%20becomes%20expensive%20because%20of%20the%20extra%20labour%20cost%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBarman%2C%20always%20keen%20to%20maximise%20his%20yield%2C%20found%20an%20innovative%20way%20to%20make%20the%20most%20of%20his%20farmland.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20my%20bay%20leaf%20plants%20grew%20four%20feet%20above%20the%20soil%2C%20I%20even%20planted%20potatoes%20and%20black%20gram%20in%20the%20space%20(8%C3%978%20feet)%20between%20trees.%20This%20helps%20fertilise%20the%20field%20and%20improves%20the%20growth%20of%20trees.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20I%20harvested%20for%20the%20first%20time%20when%20the%20trees%20were%20seven%20to%2010%20feet%20tall.%20I%20also%20do%20regular%20pruning%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20the%2047-year-old.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBay%20leaves%20are%20sorted%20into%20different%20quality%20grades%2C%20determining%20where%20they%E2%80%99re%20sent.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20best%20quality%20leaves%20are%20spotless.%20A%20leaf%20has%20A%2C%20B%2C%20and%20C%20grades.%20The%20A-grade%20quality%20is%20exported%20to%20the%20Gulf%20countries%2C%20while%20B%20and%20C%20grades%20are%20supplied%20across%20India.%20It%20has%205%25%20GST.%20The%20dried%20leaves%20are%20packed%20in%20jute%20bags%20and%20plastic%20bags%20before%20being%20dispatched%20to%20cities%20such%20as%20Bengaluru%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Mumbai%2C%20Delhi%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Haryana%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20West%20Bengal%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20trader%20Sudeb%20Sarkar%2C%20who%20currently%20leases%2014%20bay%20leaf%20gardens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20demand%20soaring%2C%20a%20structured%20but%20informal%20system%20has%20evolved.%20Farmers%20who%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20enough%20labour%20or%20resources%20often%20lease%20out%20their%20gardens%20through%20open%20tenders%20for%20a%20period%20of%20three%20to%20three-and-a-half%20years.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20best%20bidder%20gets%20the%20garden%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Sarkar.%20Once%20a%20deal%20is%20made%2C%20traders%20step%20in%2C%20bringing%20in%20skilled%20labourers%20to%20climb%20trees%20and%20harvest%20leaves%20with%20sickles.%20Women%20complete%20the%20essential%20post-harvest%20work.%20Today%2C%20North%20Dinajpur%20alone%20has%20around%20100%E2%80%93150%20such%20traders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETrading%2C%20profits%20and%20the%20challenges%20that%20come%20with%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20bay%20leaf%20farming%20brings%20in%20significant%20profits%20for%20cultivators%2C%20the%20picture%20differs%20slightly%20for%20traders%20who%20take%20on%20leased%20gardens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20pay%20Rs%201900%20per%20quintal%20labour%20cost%20for%20cutting%20twigs%2C%20leaves%2C%20stacking%2C%20and%20packing.%20Further%2C%20Rs%20700%20per%20quintal%20is%20spent%20on%20watering%20the%20trees%2C%20applying%20proper%20manure%20or%20fertiliser%2C%20and%20spraying%20insecticides%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20a%2029-year-old%20trader.%20%E2%80%9CA%20trader%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20benefit%20as%20much%20as%20a%20farmer%20does.%20With%20the%20expiry%20of%20the%20tender%2C%20the%20farmer%20gets%20back%20his%20garden.%20Some%2030%20farmers%20are%20still%20maintaining%20gardens%2C%20while%20most%20of%20the%20gardens%20are%20operated%20by%20traders.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBay%20leaf%20trading%20may%20be%20lucrative%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20without%20its%20challenges%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20plant%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EGuarding%20the%20green%20gold%3A%20tackling%20pests%20%26amp%3B%20preserving%20quality%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20its%20culinary%20appeal%