C%20but%20at%20least%20I%20could%20feed%20Giordana%2C%20change%20her%20diaper%2C%20take%20her%20on%20a%20walk%20during%20my%20lunch%20break%2C%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20go%20through%20her%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-evening-walk-bedtime-routine-calm-kids-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20bedtime%20routine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20I'm%20now%20a%20mother%20of%20three%20and%20pregnant%20with%20our%20fourth.%20In%20August%202022%2C%20my%20company%20implemented%20a%20two-day-a-week%20in-office%20mandate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20grateful%20to%20work%20for%20a%20company%20that%20understands%20the%20benefits%20of%20a%20hybrid%20schedule.%20Allowing%20me%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-weird-habits-return-to-office-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20work%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%20three%20days%20a%20week%20gives%20me%20the%20flexibility%20to%20pick%20up%20my%20kids%20from%20school%20if%20needed%2C%20take%20them%20to%20the%20doctor%20when%20they're%20sick%2C%20attend%20school%20events%20on%20the%20days%20I'm%20not%20in%20the%20office%2C%20and%20be%20home%20when%20they%20return%20from%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20about%20being%20physically%20present%20and%20being%20able%20to%20kiss%20them%20hello%20and%20ask%20how%20their%20day%20was%20before%20the%20chaos%20of%20bedtime%2C%20which%20is%20always%20tougher%20after%20a%20long%20day%20at%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20every%20HR%20email%20that%20pops%20into%20my%20inbox%20makes%20my%20stomach%20drop.%20I%20worry%20it%20will%20be%20a%20message%20about%20a%20full-time%20return-to-office%20mandate%20that%20would%20force%20me%20to%20choose%20between%20my%20career%20and%20my%20family%20responsibilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20understand%20there%20are%20some%20women%20who%20work%20in%20industries%20where%20remote%20work%20is%20impossible%2C%20but%20I%20wish%20some%20companies%20understood%20that%20forcing%20working%20mothers%20back%20into%20the%20office%20full-time%20is%20a%20mistake%2C%20especially%20when%20the%20job%20can%20be%20done%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228485%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mother%20in%20the%20backyard%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680fb634c6ad288d147f555f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225657%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20now%20hopes%20remote%20work%20won't%20be%20taken%20from%20her.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e86a3491-581f-4f61-88ed-64a97c958938%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMothers%20in%20the%20US%20are%20facing%20a%20brutal%20decision%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMothers%20dealing%20with%20full-time%20RTO%20mandates%20often%20face%20one%20of%20two%20paths%3A%20continue%20working%20full%20time%20and%20pay%20for%20childcare%20or%20quit%20the%20workforce%20to%20raise%20their%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20choices%20will%20be%20familiar%20to%20many%20women%20who%20worked%20before%20COVID.%20But%20the%20pandemic%20showed%20how%20inflexibility%20can%20cut%20both%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployment%20by%20working%20mothers%20fell%20more%20sharply%20than%20for%20other%20groups%20during%20the%20pandemic.%20The%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20found%20that%202.4%20million%20women%20left%20the%20workforce%20from%20February%202020%20to%202021%2C%20compared%20to%201.8%20million%20men.%20Women%20may%20have%20been%20disproportionately%20affected%20because%20they're%20usually%20the%20primary%20caregivers%2C%20facing%20unique%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplace%20flexibility%2C%20which%20has%20been%20the%20trend%20post-pandemic%2C%20appears%20to%20have%20helped%20reverse%20this.%20According%20to%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.dol.gov%2F2024%2F05%2F06%2Fmothers-employment-has-surpassed-pre-pandemic-levels-but-the-child-care-crisis-persists%5C%22%20target%3D%