F681e4faa3fe8d39283657803%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0Pilots%20flying%20a%20C-130%20military%20transport%20aircraft.%3Cp%3EStaff%20Sgt.%20Kylee%20Warren%2FUS%20Air%20National%20Guard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20military's%20research%20arm%20is%20researching%20how%20to%20improve%20sleep%20for%20combat%20troops%20and%20pilots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20DoD%20has%20long%20known%20that%20chronic%20sleeplessness%20can%20pose%20serious%20long-term%20health%20risks.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDARPA-funded%20light%20therapy%20devices%20could%20one%20day%20boost%20alertness%20and%20sleep%20efficiency%20without%20stimulants.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20military%20personnel%20aren't%20getting%20enough%20sleep%2C%20but%20a%20top%20Pentagon%20research%20agency%20is%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20fix%20the%20problems%20that%20come%20with%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Defense%20Advanced%20Research%20Project%20Agency%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdarpa-exploring-how-blood-biohacks-could-help-warfighters-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDARPA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20ideas%20it's%20exploring%20to%20help%20tired%20pilots%20and%20worn-out%20combat%20troops%20get%20better%20sleep%20but%20also%20stay%20awake%20when%20it's%20needed%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20common%20for%20our%20warfighters%20to%20get%20less%20than%20six%20hours%20sleep%20a%20night%2C%20which%20is%20really%20the%20definition%20of%20chronic%20sleep%20deprivation%2C%26quot%3B%20explained%20Gregory%20Witkop%2C%20a%20former%20flight%20surgeon%20who%20is%20now%20a%20DARPA%20sleep%20research%20manager.%20He%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20during%20combat%20operations%2C%20that%20number%20might%20plummet%20closer%20to%20three%20hours%20a%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELack%20of%20sleep%20can%20have%20disastrous%20consequences%20for%20the%20DoD.%20A%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-24-105917%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20watchdog%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20lack%20of%20sleep%20contributed%20to%20military%20safety%20mishaps%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2019%2F08%2F06%2Fnew-report-points-acute-fatigue-factor-deadly-navy-ship-collision.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emultiple%20deaths%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20troops%20have%20cited%20long%20work%20hours%20and%20shoddy%20barracks%20mattresses%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fblog%2Flack-sleep-has-left-our-military-less-combat-ready-and-more-prone-accidents-dire-consequences%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eobstacles%20to%20better%20sleep%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Witkop%20wants%20to%20know%20if%20his%20agency%20can%20help%20someone%20who%20only%20slept%20three%20hours%20feel%20like%20they%20got%20much%20more%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225448%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20solider%20naps%20during%20an%20event%20at%20Fort%20Knox%2C%20Kentucky%2C%20on%20May%2029th%2C%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e6168c6ad288d148092bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222404%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20solider%20naps%20during%20an%20event%20at%20Fort%20Knox%2C%20Kentucky.%3Cp%3EG.%20Anthonie%20Riis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20again%20make%20a%20normal%20sleep%20cycle%20more%20efficient%20so%20that%20we%20are%20able%20to%20get%20all%20of%20the%20benefits%20from%20both%20parts%20of%20sleep%20every%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recently%20told%20BI%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmy.clevelandclinic.org%2Fhealth%2Fbody%2F12148-sleep-basics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifferent%20depths%20of%20sleep%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20REM%20and%20non-REM.%20DARPA%20doesn't%20conduct%20its%20own%20research%2C%20but%20it%20is%20setting%20priorities%20for%20contracted%20universities%20and%20companies%20to%20look%20into%20tackling%20troop%20sleep%20troubles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Witkop%2C%20maximizing%20sleep%20success%20might%20look%20something%20like%20a%20headband%20or%20cap%20that%20emits%20targeted%20light%20waves%20to%20parts%20of%20an%20infantryman's%20brain%20while%20sleeping.%20Such%20waves%20would%20theoretically%20boost%20the%20benefits%20of%20even%20just%20three%20hours%20of%20sleep%20to%20hopefully%20feel%20more%20like%20five%20hours%20of%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20is%2C%20I%20think%2C%20under-appreciated%20about%20sleep%20in%20particular%2C%20is%20that%20we%20kind%20of%20think%20of%20it%20as%20something%20that's%20a%20'nice%20to%20have'%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20a%20'need%20to%20have'%2C%26quot%3B%20Witkop%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20understand%20why%20people%20even%20sleep%2C%20Witkop%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20it%20doesn't%20make%20much%20sense%20from%20an%20evolutionary%20point%20of%20view%20to%20be%20defenseless%20for%20so%20many%20hours.%20But%20the%20military%20has%20long%20recognized%20sleep's%20importance%20for%20troops%2C%20despite%20many%20not%20getting%20enough%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20%26quot%3Bliterally%20heals%20the%20brain%20every%20single%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20chronic%20lack%20of%20sleep%20can%20contribute%20to%20elevated%20risks%20of%20suicide%2C%20PTSD%2C%20and%20other%20health%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224624%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22U.S.%20soldiers%20sleep%20on%20a%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III%20during%20a%20redeployment%20flight%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Dec.%207%2C%202018.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e622fc6ad288d148092f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223173%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EU.S.%20soldiers%20sleep%20on%20a%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III%20during%20a%20redeployment%20flight%20from%20Afghanistan.%3Cp%3EStaff%20Sgt.%20Jordan%20Castelan%2FUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20a%20problem%20limited%20to%20military%20servicemembers.%20Most%20Americans%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-loss-deprivation-america-reasons-health-inequality-economic-stress-money-2024-5%23%3A~%3Atext%3DWhen%2520we%2520don%2527t%2520get%2Chas%2520grown%2520worse%2520over%2520time.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erunning%20on%20fumes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20sleeplessness%20exacerbated%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimproved-sleep-after-removing-phone-tv-tech-bedroom-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etelevisions%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-cant-put-down-their-phones-even-in-bed-charts-2017-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecell%20phones%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20bedrooms.%20But%20most%20Americans%20aren't%20trying%20to%20fly%20an%20aerial%20tanker%2C%20a%20flying%20gas%20station%20for%20complex%20aerial%20refueling%20maneuvers%2C%20or%20put%20fire%20down%20range%20without%20accidentally%20hitting%20their%20comrades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETroops%20need%20to%20be%20well%20rested%2C%20Witkop%20said%2C%20or%20at%20least%20feel%20like%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20DARPA's%20not%20just%20focused%20on%20getting%20troops%20better%20rest.%20The%20research%20arm%20also%20wants%20to%20know%20how%20it%20can%20help%20troops%20like%20pilots%2C%20who%20regularly%20fly%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20or%20pull%20long%20combat%20hours%2C%20stay%20awake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnyone%20who%20has%20ever%20driven%20home%20late%20at%20night%20fueled%20by%20coffee%20knows%20the%20feeling%20of%20trying%20to%20fall%20asleep%20after%20arriving%20but%20still%20being%20wired%20in%20bed%20thanks%20to%20caffeine%2C%20said%20Pedro%20Irazoqui%2C%20who%20oversees%20another%20DARPA%20sleep%20research%20project.%20That's%20especially%20true%20for%20pilots%2C%20one%20of%20Irazoqui's%20target%20populations%20for%20a%20different%20type%20of%20headband-type%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThink%20of%20a%20pilot%20flying%2010%20to%2020%20hours%2C%20and%20having%20to%20stay%20awake%20and%20pilot%20an%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20then%20at%20the%20end%20of%20that%20long%20flight%2C%20having%20to%20land%20that%20aircraft%20maybe%20not%20under%20ideal%20conditions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20want%20them%20to%20be%20as%20awake%20and%20alert%20as%20they%20possibly%20can%20be%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225568%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22U.S.%20soldiers%20sleep%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20a%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III%2C%20Aug.%2017%2C%202019.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681e63ce3fe8d39283657d9a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223712%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20sleep%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20a%20C-17%20Globemaster%20III.%3Cp%3EStaff%20Sgt.%20Alex%20Manne%2FUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20often%20ends%20up%20happening%2C%20Irazoqui%20said%2C%20is%20that%20pilots%20will%20chug%20an%20energy%20drink%20just%20before%20their%20final%20approach%20to%20make%20sure%20they're%20locked%20in%2C%20leading%20to%20more%20caffeine%20the%20next%20day%20to%20again%20fight%20fatigue%20again%20while%20flying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20safe%2C%20and%20that's%20not%20good%20for%20quality%20of%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20he%20wants%20to%20help%20pilots%20stay%20awake%20with%20another%20form%20of%20light%20therapy%2C%20infrared%20light%2C%20making%20them%20feel%20as%20if%20they%20have%20had%20a%20jolt%20from%20an%20energy%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20that%20light%20is%20switched%20off%2C%20stimulation%20could%20cease%20immediately%2C%20allowing%20the%20pilot%20to%20rapidly%20tra