when%20I%20brought%20AJ%20home%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20I%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpostpartum-depression-rates-doubled-women-describe-symptoms-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrantically%20crying%20and%20hysterical%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20I%20didn't%20have%20any%20newborn%20clothes.%20I%20didn't%20even%20know%20they%20existed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f3341a6-a620-43d7-b1fd-d20fdd29e856%5C%22%3EI%20want%20back%20to%20work%20after%203%20months%20of%20maternity%20leave%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20took%20paternity%20leave%2C%20and%20my%20mother%20came%20to%20town%20to%20help%20me%20with%20the%20baby%2C%20but%20I%20was%20still%20struggling.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-show-the-painful-realities-of-breastfeeding-2020-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBreastfeeding%20was%20very%20painful%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20AJ%20was%20a%20horrible%20sleeper.%20My%20hormones%20were%20out%20of%20whack%2C%20my%20world%20had%20shifted%2C%20I%20was%20isolated%20in%20a%20new%20city%2C%20and%20small%20things%20would%20set%20me%20over%20the%20edge.%20Everything%20scared%20me.%20I%20don't%20remember%20feeling%20any%20joy%20as%20a%20new%20mom%20until%20AJ%20was%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20I%20convinced%20myself%20that%20how%20I%20was%20feeling%20was%20normal%2C%20but%20looking%20back%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fhow-long-does-postpartum-depression-last%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20was%20depressed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mom%20holding%20baby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67fe7e43c6ad288d147e2fed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20Hollingsworth%20didn't%20know%20what%20was%20normal%20after%20giving%20birth%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Sarah%20Hollingsworth%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20done%20this%20to%20identify%20that%20something%20was%20wrong.%20I%20wasn't%20even%20meeting%20my%20own%20self-care%20and%20basic%20needs.%20I%20had%20literally%20stopped%20brushing%20my%20teeth%20%E2%80%94%20that%20wasn't%20normal%3B%20it%20was%20a%20red%20flag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20three%20months%20of%20maternity%20leave%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-went-back-to-work-five-weeks-after-giving-birth-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewent%20back%20to%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Remote%20working%20wasn't%20a%20thing%20at%20the%20time.%20I%20was%20expected%20to%20work%20from%20the%20office%20in%20San%20Antonio.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20wake%20up%20at%206%20a.m.%20to%20get%20on%20the%20road%20by%207%20a.m.%20in%20order%20to%20be%20at%20the%20shuttle%20stop%20by%207%3A35%20a.m.%20I'd%20be%20at%20the%20office%20from%208%3A30%20a.m.%2C%20working%20all%20day%20until%203%20p.m.%20I%20often%20pumped%20breast%20milk%20on%20the%20shuttle%20and%20at%20work.%20On%20the%20way%20home%2C%20I%20collected%20my%20daughter%20from%20day%20care%20and%20would%20have%2030%20minutes%20with%20her%20before%20putting%20her%20to%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20neglecting%20my%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225252f9bd-047a-42a8-8a55-580f18d6938e%5C%22%3EI%20was%20afraid%20to%20tell%20people%20how%20I%20was%20feeling%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20body%20started%20to%20show%20signs%20of%20stress.%20I%20broke%20out%20in%20bumps%20and%20blisters%20all%20over%20my%20hands%2C%20melasma%2C%20and%20had%20severe%20Perioral%20Dermatitis%20on%20my%20face.%20It%20was%20humiliating%20to%20go%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20my%20lowest%20point%2C%20in%20January%202020%2C%20I%20remember%20driving%20to%20work%2C%20because%20I%20had%20missed%20the%20shuttle%2C%20wondering%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20I%20hit%20the%20car%20in